# EchoPark Design System (EPDS) — Project Knowledge

## Documentation sources (read and follow)
- **This file** (`.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc`) is `alwaysApply: true` for the globs below — it is the **single** EPDS reference: tokens, components, Storybook, library packaging, icons, accessibility, and Figma workflow. Update it when conventions change.

## Stack
- **Framework**: Vue 3 with `<script setup>` + TypeScript (Composition API only — no Options API)
- **Build**: Vite 8, `@vitejs/plugin-vue`, `vite-svg-loader`; **library bundle** via `vite.lib.config.ts` + `vite-plugin-dts`
- **Docs**: Storybook 10 (`@storybook/vue3-vite`) — addons: docs, a11y (errors on violation), pseudo-states, Chromatic
- **Styling**: Three-layer CSS custom property system (primitives → semantic → scales); scoped `<style>` blocks in SFCs
- **Token TS wrapper**: `src/tokens/tokens.ts`
- **Breakpoints**: `src/tokens/breakpoints.ts` (JS constants — CSS vars can't be used in `@media`)
- **Font**: Roboto via Google Fonts (weights 300/400/500/700/900) — loaded in `index.html` and `.storybook/preview-head.html`. Weight 900 (Black) is used by `NavItem` Active state per the Sonic spec.
- **Path aliases**: `@/` → `src/`, `@icons/` → `icon/`, `@logos/` → `Logos/`, `@illustrations/` → `Illustrations/`

