### `SelectDropdown` — `src/components/SelectDropdown/`
- **Figma**: "Inputs/Dropdowns" — underline-style native select with floating label
- **Props**: `label: string` (**required**), `options: SelectOption[]` (**required**, `{ value, label }`), `modelValue?: string`, `theme?: 'light' | 'dark'`, `disabled?: boolean`, `error?: string`, `name?: string`
- **Emits**: `update:modelValue: [value: string]`
- **Architecture**: Uses the device's **native `<select>`** element (`appearance: none`) per Figma build guideline ("Clicking the form will open that device's native menu/list")
- **Floating label**: Sits at input text level when empty (acts as grey placeholder); floats 12px above the control when a value is selected (`hasValue` computed). CSS `transition` animates the movement.
- **Underline only** — no box border. 2px line at bottom of the 34px control area.
- **Fixed control height**: 34px regardless of state or error. Error text is `position: absolute; top: 38px` so it never shifts layout.
- **Chevron**: `icon/Style=Arrows, Detail=No-Tail, Icon=Down.svg?raw` rendered with `v-html`, `fill: currentColor` via `:deep(path)`
- **States**: Default (empty), Filled (has value), Focused (Accessibility80 line), Disabled, Error
- **Light theme colors**: label grey=Neutral40 → float to Neutral70; value text Neutral0; line Neutral80; error `--color-warning-40` (#B30715)
- **Dark theme colors**: label/line Neutral85; value text white; focused line Accessibility80; error `#fa848e`; disabled hides the line entirely
- **Stories**: LightDefault, LightFilled, LightError, LightFilledError, LightDisabledFilled, DarkDefault, DarkFilled, DarkError, DarkDisabledFilled, AllStatesLight, AllStatesDark, WidthVariants, Interactive

