### `CompareButton` — `src/components/CompareButton/`
- **Figma**: "Buttons/Compare" — 32×32 pill-shaped toggle used on SRP tiles to add/remove a vehicle from the compare list. Figma only defines six states (Un-added / Added × default / hover / focus); there is no disabled state.
- **Props**: `selected?: boolean` (v-model via `v-model:selected`), `compareLabel?: string` (default `'Compare'`), `removeLabel?: string` (default `'Remove'`), `ariaLabelUnselected?: string` (default `'Add to compare'`), `ariaLabelSelected?: string` (default `'Remove from compare'`)
- **Emits**: `update:selected: [boolean]`, `click: [event: MouseEvent]`
- **Behaviour**: Hover/focus expands the pill **to the left** to reveal the label (animated via `grid-template-columns: 0fr → 1fr`, 0.25s). Click toggles `selected`. Mouse off collapses back to the circle. Icon switches from `+` (Add.svg) when unselected to ✓ (Check.svg) when selected.
- **No-bounce rule**: The component renders as a 32×32 `position: relative` anchor slot containing a `position: absolute; right: 0` button. This pins the button's right edge regardless of parent layout (normal flow, flex, grid, absolute) — the button grows **leftward** only. `padding-right` is also held constant at 3px so the icon stays exactly 4px (border + pad) from the outer right edge throughout the animation. `z-index: 1` is applied on hover/focus so the expanded pill sits above adjacent content.
- **States**:
  - Un-added (default): 32×32 white circle, 1px `--color-neutral-90` border, `+` icon in **`--color-action-primary`** (green for EchoPark, red for Sonic)
  - Un-added hover/focus: expanded pill with "Compare" label in `--color-neutral-0`; `+` icon stays `--color-action-primary`; focus swaps border to `--color-focus-ring`
  - Added (default): 32×32 `--color-action-primary` circle, 1px `--color-neutral-90` border, white check icon
  - Added hover/focus: expanded pill with "Remove" label in white; focus swaps border to `--color-focus-ring`
- **Icon vs label colour**: icon colour is controlled on `.compare-btn__icon` (brand-primary when unselected, white when selected) — it is intentionally **decoupled** from the label text colour so the unselected `+` can remain brand-coloured while the hover label renders in dark `Neutral0`.
- **Brand awareness**: Both the unselected icon colour and the selected fill use `--color-action-primary`, so the button automatically themes green (EchoPark) or red (Sonic) — no brand prop needed.
- **Dimensions**: 32×32 collapsed; height fixed at 32px when expanded (padding `0 3px 0 8px`, 5px gap, 24×24 icon on right, 14px Roboto Medium label on left)
- **Accessibility**: `aria-pressed` reflects `selected`; `aria-label` is always applied (not a decorative button); focus ring uses `--color-focus-ring`
- **Icons**: `icon/Style=Display, Detail=Default, Icon=Add.svg?raw` and `icon/Style=Display, Detail=Default, Icon=Check.svg?raw`, both rendered via `v-html` so `:deep(path) { fill: currentColor }` inherits the icon wrapper's `color`
- **Usage**: Designed for the SRP tile — see `SrpTile` integration below. `SrpTile` places the button 16px from the tile's right edge, straddling the image/content boundary on the same horizontal line as the carousel dots. In standalone use the component renders a 32×32 anchor slot that reserves layout space while the button absolutely positions over it (`position: absolute; right: 0`), so the icon stays pinned when the pill expands to the left — works inside flex, grid, or positioned parents.
- **SrpTile integration**: `SrpTile` exposes `compared?: boolean` (`v-model:compared`) and emits `update:compared`. The button is placed via `.srpt__compare` at `bottom: 0; right: 16px; transform: translateY(50%); z-index: 6;` inside the image area — above the carousel dots (z-index 5) so the hover expansion never gets clipped. Click handler calls `preventDefault()` + `stopPropagation()` so the underlying `srpt__image-link` does not navigate to the VDP.
- **Stories**: UnaddedDefault, UnaddedHover, UnaddedFocus, AddedDefault, AddedHover, AddedFocus, AllStates, Interactive, SrpTileContext
- **Storybook `title`**: `Atoms/Buttons/CompareButton`

### `CompareTray` — `src/components/CompareTray/`
- **Figma**: nodes `13945:38154` (count + CTA) and `13945:38159` (prompt-only) — floating notification card that appears once the user flags a vehicle on an SRP tile.
- **Props**: `count: number` (**required** — vehicles currently in the compare list), `ctaThreshold?: number` (default `2`), `addMoreLabel?: string` (default `'Add more to compare'`), `selectedLabel?: string` (default `'vehicles selected'`), `compareLabel?: string` (default `'Compare'`), `ariaLabel?: string`
- **Emits**: `compare: [event: MouseEvent]` — fired when the user clicks the **Compare** CTA (parent routes to the compare page).
- **Behaviour**:
  - `count === 0` → the component renders nothing (tray is hidden).
  - `0 < count < ctaThreshold` → 85px card with the **prompt** text only (`addMoreLabel`).
  - `count >= ctaThreshold` → 149px card showing `<count> {selectedLabel}` (count is bold, rest Light 300) plus a 148×56 `BaseButton variant="primary"` labelled `compareLabel`.
- **Layout**:
  - **Desktop (≥600px)**: 412px fixed-width card, `position: fixed; right: 0; bottom: 0; z-index: 900`, shadow `-4px -4px 20.7px rgba(0,0,0,0.16)` (falls up-and-left so the card reads as floating above page content).
  - **Mobile (<600px)**: stretches to 100vw, pinned to the bottom of the viewport, shadow changes to `0 -4px 20.7px rgba(0,0,0,0.16)` (straight up).
- **Animation**: fade + slide-up on enter/leave (`transition: transform 0.25s ease, opacity 0.2s ease`). `@media (prefers-reduced-motion)` drops the transform.
- **Typography**: Prompt + count label share Roboto Light 22px, line-height 1.2, `--color-neutral-0`. The count number is `font-weight: 700`.
- **Brand awareness**: The CTA uses `BaseButton variant="primary"` so the filled background automatically themes `--color-action-primary` (green for EchoPark, red for Sonic).
- **Accessibility**: Rendered as a `<aside role="status" aria-live="polite">` so assistive tech announces state changes. `aria-label` defaults to a human-readable description of the current state and can be overridden via the `ariaLabel` prop.
- **SrpPage integration**: `SrpPage` derives `comparedCount = listings.filter(l => l.compared).length` and renders `<CompareTray :count="comparedCount" @compare="onCompareAction" />` once at the page root (after `GlobalFooter`, outside the `Teleport`). `onCompareAction` will eventually route to the compare page.
- **Stories**: AddMorePrompt, TwoSelected, ThreeSelected, Hidden, Interactive, Mobile
- **Storybook `title`**: `Molecules/CompareTray`

