### `NavItem` — `src/components/NavItem/`
- **Figma**: Single component covering both Figma variants — "Navigation / no dropdown" (node `7639:20395`) and "Navigation / with dropdown" (node `7639:20405`). First atoms of the global header / nav organism.
- **Props**: `label?: string` (alternatively use the default slot), `active?: boolean` (default `false` — current page on no-dropdown, open menu on dropdown — supports `v-model:active`), `dropdown?: boolean` (default `false` — show trailing 24×24 chevron), `href?: string` (renders as `<a>` when set), `target?: string`, `ariaLabel?: string`
- **Emits**: `update:active: [value: boolean]`, `click: [event: MouseEvent]`
- **Click semantics**: The component toggles `active` itself (via `update:active`) **only for the dropdown variant** — clicking a dropdown trigger emits the next active value so it works as `v-model:active` out of the box (open / close menu). **Plain nav links never toggle on click** — they navigate, and the parent app sets `active` from the current route. Both variants always emit `click` for analytics / `preventDefault` interception.
- **Renders as**: `<button>` by default; `<a>` when `href` is provided. No-dropdown active anchors get `aria-current="page"`; no-dropdown active buttons get `aria-pressed="true"`. Dropdown variants always wire `aria-haspopup="true"` and surface `aria-expanded` from `active`.
- **Anatomy**: 8 px-gap inline-flex of `[label]` + optional `[chevron]`. Chevron is the bundled `Style=Arrows, Detail=No-Tail, Icon=Down.svg` rendered at 24 × 24 via `?raw` + `v-html`; it rotates 180 ° when `active` is true (re-uses the single Down asset rather than shipping an Up duplicate). `:deep(path) { fill: currentColor }` lets the chevron track the same colour as the label across all states.
- **States** (Figma):
 - **Default** — Roboto Regular 16 px, line-height 1, letter-spacing -0.032 px, `--color-nav-text` (`#292B2E`); chevron points Down
 - **Hover** (only when not active) — `--color-nav-text-hover` (`#445366`) + underline on the label only (`text-underline-offset: 2px`, `text-decoration-skip-ink: none`); chevron stays Down
 - **Active** (current page / open menu) — Roboto **Black 900**, `--color-nav-text-active` (`#292B2E`); no underline; chevron flipped Up; hover styling is suppressed while active
 - **Focus** (`:focus-visible`) — 3 px solid `--color-nav-focus-ring` (Accessibility90 `#6FCFFF`) + `--color-nav-text-focus` (`#566F8F`); active items keep their bold weight + Up chevron while showing the focus border
- **Layout-stable focus ring**: `border: 3px solid transparent` + `padding: 0 4px` are reserved at all times so toggling `:focus-visible` never shifts the surrounding nav bar.
- **Brand awareness**: All colour comes from `--color-nav-*` tokens defined in **both** `primitives/echopark.css` and `primitives/sonic.css` with **identical Figma values** for now (the SA-derived design is the global default — both brand modes render the same nav appearance until a brand explicitly redefines them). The component still ships `var()` fallbacks (`--color-neutral-0`, `--color-action-accent`, `--color-action-accent-muted`, `--color-focus-ring`) for any future brand that doesn't declare nav tokens. Font follows `--font-family-brand`.
- **Roboto Black (900)**: Loaded in `index.html` and `.storybook/preview-head.html` (`...family=Roboto:wght@300;400;500;700;900...`) — required for the Active state. Falls back to `bold` (700) if the weight isn't loaded.
- **Stories**: `Default`, `Hover`, `Active`, `FocusSelected`, `DropdownDefault`, `DropdownHover`, `DropdownActive`, `DropdownFocus`, `AsAnchor`, `ActiveAnchor`, `AllStates`, `AllStatesDropdown`, `DropdownInteractive` (click-to-toggle demo), `NavBarPreview` (single-open dropdown bar).
- **Storybook `title`**: `Atoms/Navigation/NavItem`

