### `MenuToggle` — `src/components/MenuToggle/`
- **Figma**: "Hamburger menu / closed" (node `7639:20490` — closed/hamburger icon states) and the open/X states immediately below (node `7639:20520`).
- **Role**: Mobile menu hamburger / close toggle. Renders the hamburger icon when the drawer is closed and the X (close) icon when it's open. Click toggles `open` automatically — works as `v-model:open` out of the box, matching the same pattern as `NavItem` (dropdown variant) and `CompareButton`.
- **Props**: `open?: boolean` (default `false` — `true` shows X, `false` shows hamburger), `ariaLabel?: string` (override; defaults to `'Open menu'` / `'Close menu'`), `disabled?: boolean`
- **Emits**: `update:open: [value: boolean]`, `click: [event: MouseEvent]`
- **Renders as**: `<button type="button">` only — never an anchor. `aria-expanded` and `aria-pressed` both reflect `open`.
- **Icons**: Bundled from `icon/Style=Display, Detail=Menu, Icon=Menu.svg` (hamburger) and `icon/Style=Display, Detail=Default, Icon=Close.svg` (X), imported with `?raw` and rendered via `v-html`. Both inherit `currentColor` via `:deep(path) { fill: currentColor }` so all four state colours flow through the icon automatically.
- **Layout**: `display: inline-flex; width: 30px; height: 30px; box-sizing: border-box; border: 3px solid transparent`. Inner icon area is always `24 × 24`. The 3 px transparent border reserves focus-ring space at all times — toggling `:focus-visible` never shifts the surrounding header layout.
- **States** (Figma):
 - **Default** — `--color-nav-text` (`#292B2E`)
 - **Hover** — `--color-nav-text-hover` (`#445366`)
 - **Pressed** — `--color-nav-text-focus` (`#566F8F`); fired transiently via `:active` (touch / mouse press)
 - **Focus** (`:focus-visible`) — 3 px solid `--color-nav-focus-ring` (Accessibility90 `#6FCFFF`); icon colour stays at the default
 - **Disabled** — `opacity: var(--opacity-level-medium)` + `cursor: not-allowed`
- **Brand awareness**: Uses the global `--color-nav-*` tokens (defined identically in `primitives/echopark.css` and `primitives/sonic.css`) so behaviour matches `NavItem` / `NavItemMobile` / `NavItemSubmenu` across brands with no component changes.
- **Stories**: `ClosedDefault`, `ClosedHover`, `ClosedPressed`, `ClosedFocus`, `OpenDefault`, `OpenHover`, `OpenPressed`, `OpenFocus`, `Disabled`, `AllStates` (8-cell grid: closed × open × four states), `Interactive` (ref-backed `v-model:open` demo).
- **Storybook `title`**: `Atoms/Navigation/MenuToggle`

### `NavIconButton` — `src/components/NavIconButton/`
- **Figma**: Favorites heart (node `7639:21078` — Figma calls the frame "Hamburger menu" but it's the heart icon) and Profile avatar (node `7639:21038`). Same four-state machine drives both, so they share one primitive.
- **Role**: Generic 24 × 24 nav-area icon button. Used by the global header for the Favorites heart, Profile avatar, and any future single-icon nav action (Cart, Notifications, etc.). Pure shape primitive — the consumer passes the SVG via the `#icon` slot and decides where the click goes.
- **Props**: `ariaLabel: string` (**required**, no visible text), `selected?: boolean` (default `false` — persistent "current page" state), `href?: string` (renders as `<a>` when set), `target?: string`, `disabled?: boolean`
- **Slots**: `#icon` — 24 × 24 SVG. Import the SVG with `?raw` and wrap in `<span v-html="..." />`. The icon inherits `currentColor` via `:deep(path|circle|rect|polygon|polyline|ellipse) { fill: currentColor }`, so all four state colours flow through automatically without per-state SVG assets.
- **Emits**: `click: [event: MouseEvent]`
- **Renders as**: `<button type="button">` by default; `<a>` when `href` is provided. Selected anchors get `aria-current="page"`; selected buttons get `aria-pressed="true"`. Disabled anchors get `aria-disabled="true"` + `pointer-events: none`.
- **States** (Figma):
 - **Default** — `--color-nav-text` (`#292B2E`)
 - **Hover** — `--color-nav-text-hover` (`#445366`)
 - **Pressed** (`:active`) **and Selected** — `--color-nav-text-focus` (`#566F8F`); `selected` is the persistent "current page" indicator (icon equivalent of the bold active state on `NavItem` — icons can't bold, so the design uses colour instead)
 - **Focus** (`:focus-visible`) — 3 px solid `--color-nav-focus-ring` (Accessibility90 `#6FCFFF`); icon colour stays at the underlying state colour
 - **Disabled** — `opacity: var(--opacity-level-medium)` + `pointer-events: none`
- **Layout-stable focus ring**: `width: 30px; height: 30px; box-sizing: border-box; border: 3px solid transparent`. Inner icon area is always 24 × 24. Mirrors `MenuToggle` exactly.
- **Brand awareness**: Uses the global `--color-nav-*` tokens (defined identically in `primitives/echopark.css` and `primitives/sonic.css`) so behaviour matches the rest of the nav family across brands with no component changes.
- **Stories** (favorites + profile, plus shared variants): `FavoritesDefault`, `FavoritesHover`, `FavoritesPressed`, `FavoritesSelected` (current page), `FavoritesFocus`, `ProfileDefault`, `ProfileHover`, `ProfilePressed`, `ProfileSelected`, `ProfileFocus`, `AsAnchor`, `AllStates` (8-cell grid: heart × profile × four visible states), `HeaderRowPreview` (both icons composed side-by-side with click-to-toggle `selected` demo).
- **Storybook `title`**: `Atoms/Navigation/NavIconButton`

