### Brand configuration pattern (GlobalHeader + GlobalFooter)
Both site chrome components follow the same pattern: **EchoPark content is the default; other brands override via props.** This keeps the components reusable without duplication.
- **Colours** adapt automatically via the semantic token / primitives swap (e.g. `--color-action-primary` becomes red for Sonic).
- **Content** (logos, links, badges, phone numbers) is passed as structured props.
- **Storybook** stories for each brand demonstrate the configuration; use the Brand toolbar toggle to preview colour theming.

### `SonicNavBar` — `src/components/SonicNavBar/`
- **Figma**: "Frame 2492" (node `7639:20938`) — single nav frame with five Property 1 variants. **Default** (desktop bar, 1440×72), **Variant 2** (mobile bar, 375×64), **Variant 3** (desktop with mega-menu open, 1440×412), **Variant 4** (mobile drawer with parent list, 375×552), **Variant 5** (mobile drawer drilled into a parent submenu, 375×952).
- **Role**: Sonic-style global navigation organism. Composes every nav atom in the system: `NavItem` (desktop primary nav + dropdown triggers), `NavItemMobile` (mobile drawer parent rows), `NavItemSubmenu` (drilled submenu leaf links), `MenuToggle` (hamburger / close), `NavIconButton` (favourites + profile), `BaseButton` (primary CTA), `Divider` (mobile drilled-submenu separator).
- **Props**: `navItems: NavBarItem[]` (**required**), `logoUrl?: string` (default Sonic SA-FullColor logo), `logoHref?: string` (default `'/'`), `brandName?: string` (default `'Sonic Automotive'`, used for alt + aria labels), `ctaLabel?: string` (default `'Join the Sonic Circuit'`), `ctaHref?: string`, `favoritesHref?: string` (default `'/favorites'`), `profileHref?: string` (default `'/account'`), `favoritesSelected?: boolean`, `profileSelected?: boolean`, `forceMobile?: boolean` (Storybook escape hatch — applies the mobile layout regardless of the viewport media query so narrow canvas frames render correctly), `sticky?: boolean` (default `true`) — pin the bar to the viewport top with `position: sticky`. Pages with their own top-of-viewport sticky elements (e.g. `SrpPage`'s filter sidebar at `top: 0`) should pass `:sticky="false"` so the bar scrolls away normally and the page-level sticky takes over.
- **Type exports**:
 - `NavBarLink` — `{ label: string, href?: string }`
 - `NavBarSection` — `{ heading: string, links: NavBarLink[] }`
 - `NavBarItem` — `{ key: string, label: string, href?: string, dropdown?: NavBarSection[] }`. When `dropdown` is omitted the item is a direct link (e.g. "Sell/Trade"). When supplied, the item becomes a desktop dropdown trigger and a drilled-mobile parent row.
- **Emits**: `cta-click`, `favorites-click`, `profile-click`, `submenu-link-click: [{ item, link, event }]`, `nav-item-click: [{ item, event }]`.
- **Layout** (toolbar):
 - **Desktop** (≥ 1024 px): 72 px height, 80 px horizontal padding. Logo (104 × 41 px) + horizontal nav (49 px gap between items) + favourites/profile + primary CTA (`BaseButton variant="primary" size="sm"`).
 - **Mobile** (< 1024 px or `forceMobile`): 64 px height, 24 px horizontal padding. Logo (94 × 37 px) + favourites/profile + `MenuToggle`. Desktop nav and CTA are hidden via media query.
- **Mega-menu** (Variant 3 — desktop only):
 - Opens flush below the toolbar with `border-top: 1px solid var(--color-nav-active-indicator)` (Sonic dark red `#D9320D`, EchoPark green) — the "this is the live nav surface" cue.
 - 80 px / 40 px padding. Section columns laid out with **`gap: 119px`** to match Figma. The second section auto-wraps into a 2-column grid via `grid-template-columns: repeat(2, …)` so long type lists ("ATVs / UTVs / Motorcycles / Watercraft") flow into a second column.
 - Section heading: 18 px Bold; links: 16 px Regular `--color-nav-text`, hover → `--color-nav-text-hover` + underline; focus ring: 3 px `--color-nav-focus-ring` outline.
 - Only one dropdown is open at a time. Click another to swap; click the active trigger again — or click outside / press `Escape` — to close.
- **Mobile drawer** (Variant 4 + 5):
 - Slides in below the 64 px bar with the same brand-coloured `border-top`. Body scroll locks while open (mirrors `Overlay`).
 - **Parent list (Variant 4)**: vertical stack of `NavItemMobile` rows (40 px gap). Items with `dropdown` chevron-right and drill in on click; items without `dropdown` route via their `href` and emit `nav-item-click`. CTA button pinned to the bottom (`margin-top: auto`) at full width.
 - **Drilled submenu (Variant 5)**: back-arrow header (`Style=Arrows, Detail=No-Tail, Icon=Left.svg` + 20 px Black 900 parent label) on top, then each section as a labelled block (`Section heading` 18 px Bold + `NavItemSubmenu` list with 32 px gap), separated by `Divider color="light"` between sections. Same drill-in / drill-out pattern as the SRP filter panel — tap back or press `Escape` to return to the parent list.
- **Keyboard**: `Escape` collapses one level at a time — drilled submenu → parent drawer → desktop dropdown.
- **Brand awareness**: Component itself is brand-agnostic. CTA themes red on Sonic / green on EchoPark via `BaseButton variant="primary"`. Mega-menu / drawer top border reads from `--color-nav-active-indicator` (Sonic `#D9320D`, EchoPark `var(--color-base-primary-50)`). All nav text colours come from the global `--color-nav-*` family already shared across `NavItem` / `NavItemMobile` / `NavItemSubmenu` / `MenuToggle` / `NavIconButton`. The "Sonic" name reflects the Figma source frame; the underlying organism is fully white-labellable via the brand toolbar.
- **Stories** (`Organisms/SonicNavBar`): `Default` (desktop bar with placeholder body), `Variant 2 — mobile bar` (375 px frame), `Variant 3 — desktop mega-menu open` (auto-clicks "Shop rides" on mount so the mega-menu is visible without interaction), `Variant 4 — mobile drawer parent list` (auto-opens the drawer), `Variant 5 — mobile drilled submenu` (auto-opens drawer → drills into "Shop rides"), `Interactive` (fully interactive sandbox with a tall placeholder body and `layout: 'fullscreen'`).
- **Token additions**: `--color-nav-active-indicator` added to **both** `primitives/echopark.css` and `primitives/sonic.css`. EchoPark maps it to `var(--color-base-primary-50)` (brand green); Sonic maps it to `var(--color-btn-primary-surface-hover)` (`#D9320D`, the dark-red press surface).
- **Storybook `title`**: `Organisms/SonicNavBar`

