## Token Architecture (White-Label)

The token system has three layers loaded in order:

| Layer | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Primitives** | `src/tokens/primitives/echopark.css` (or `sonic.css`) | Concrete brand values: color palette + `--font-family-brand` |
| **Semantic** | `src/tokens/semantic.css` | Intent aliases mapping purpose → primitive |
| **Scales** | `src/tokens/tokens.css` | Brand-agnostic: spacing, border, shadow, opacity, typography |

### Registered brands

| Brand | Primitives file | Font | Primary | Accent |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| EchoPark | `primitives/echopark.css` | Roboto (300/400/500/700) | Green (#3E8500) | Blue (#006FA6) |
| Sonic Automotive | `primitives/sonic.css` | Roboto (300/400/500/700) | Red (#EE4128) | Steel blue (#2B4560) |

**To white-label for a new brand:** create `primitives/brand-b.css`, redefine the color vars and `--font-family-brand`, then point `src/epds.css` at that primitives file (or swap the `@import` there) — `main.ts`, Storybook `preview.ts`, and library consumers all pull tokens through `epds.css`. No component changes needed.

### Storybook brand toggle
A **Brand** dropdown in the Storybook toolbar (`.storybook/preview.ts`) switches between EchoPark and Sonic at dev time. The decorator injects the Sonic primitives CSS as a runtime override — no rebuild needed. Both brand fonts are loaded in `.storybook/preview-head.html`.

### Semantic token groups
- `--color-action-primary[-hover|-press|-vivid|-subtle]` — primary brand CTA color
- `--color-action-accent[-hover|-press|-active|-muted|-tint|-subtle]` — secondary/link color
- `--color-focus-ring` — universal focus indicator
- `--color-surface-disabled`, `--color-text-disabled` — disabled state
- `--color-feedback-error[-text|-surface]` — error/destructive states
- `--color-feedback-warning[-surface]` — caution states
- `--color-feedback-success[-surface]` — success/confirmation states
- `--color-feedback-info[-surface]` — informational/notification states
- `--color-nav-text[-hover|-active|-focus]`, `--color-nav-focus-ring` — global navigation colours; defined identically in both `primitives/echopark.css` and `primitives/sonic.css` (SA-derived nav design is the global default for now). Used by `NavItem` and future nav atoms.

### Font family chain
`--font-family-brand` (primitives) → `--font-family-base` (tokens.css) → `--font-family-btn` (tokens.css)

## Design Token Rules
- **Always** use CSS custom properties — never hardcode raw color/spacing/radius/typography values
- **In component `<style scoped>` blocks**, use semantic tokens (`--color-action-primary`, `--color-focus-ring`, etc.) for any brand-variable color. Use primitive tokens (`--color-neutral-*`, `--color-neutral-secondary-*`) only for structural neutrals that are unlikely to differ by brand.
- When adding a new token, add to both the appropriate CSS file AND `tokens.ts` simultaneously
- Figma variable defs are the source of truth; screenshot supplements when vars aren't returned
- Old/legacy aliases (`warmgray-*`, `parkgray-70`, `green-50`, `--color-parkgray-0`, `--color-white`) are NOT to be used in components

## Component Rules
- Every component in its own folder: `src/components/ComponentName/`
- **Library**: export new components from `src/index.ts` after adding `ComponentName/index.ts` (and export shared types the same way as existing entries).
- Use `<script setup lang="ts">`, `defineProps<{}>()`, `defineEmits<{}>()` — no Options API
- `<style scoped>` only — no global selectors in component files
- No inline styles unless dynamically computed
- **Reuse first**: before new markup, check whether an existing component (`BaseButton`, `LinkCta`, `Alert`, `Accordion`, etc.) already fits. Do not add hidden one-off primitives inside larger components without explicit sign-off.
- **No new sub-components without checking the user** — if a composite needs a new primitive, propose it first.
- **Vue + TypeScript templates**: on **child SFCs**, bind props using the **camelCase name from `defineProps`** (e.g. `ariaLabel`, not `aria-label`). `vue-tsc` treats DOM-style `aria-label` as a separate attribute and will report required props missing.

## Storybook Rules
- Stories co-located in component folder, CSF3 format (`satisfies Meta<typeof Component>`)
- Use `storybook-addon-pseudo-states` for hover/active/focus-visible stories
- a11y is set to `'error'` — failing stories must be fixed, not suppressed
- **Top-level sidebar groups**: **`Atoms`**, **`Molecules`**, **`Organisms`**, **`Pages`**, **`Components`**. Set each story’s `title` on `Meta`; order is controlled in **`.storybook/preview.ts`** via the inline `storySort` comparator (`order` array — **must stay inline** for Storybook 10 static analysis; **no TypeScript types inside that function**).
  - **Atoms — Buttons / CTAs**: `'Atoms/Buttons/ComponentName'` — e.g. `BaseButton`, `LinkCta`, `IconButton`, `TileCta`, `MediumIconButton`, `SmallIconButton`, `OverlayIconButton`, `CompareButton`, `ArrowCircleButton`, `VideoControlButton`, `JourneySelector`
  - **Atoms — Inputs**: `'Atoms/Inputs/ComponentName'` — e.g. `TextBoxSM`, `TextBoxLG`, `TextField`, `BaseSlider`, `BaseRadio`, `BaseCheckbox`, `BaseToggle`, `SegmentedControl`, `SelectDropdown`, `LogicSelector`, `BoxSelector`
  - **Atoms — Box inputs (sub-folder)**: `'Atoms/Inputs/Box Input/XS'` (and `/SM`, `/MD`, `/LG`)
 - **Atoms — Navigation**: `'Atoms/Navigation/NavItem'`, `'Atoms/Navigation/NavItemMobile'`, `'Atoms/Navigation/NavItemSubmenu'`, `'Atoms/Navigation/MenuToggle'`, `'Atoms/Navigation/NavIconButton'` — atoms for the global header / nav organism
  - **Atoms — asset galleries** (`src/stories/`): `'Atoms/Icons'`, `'Atoms/Illustrations'`, `'Atoms/Logos'` — **no** `Foundations/` parent
  - **Molecules** (flat `Molecules/Name` or sub-folder): `'Molecules/Accordion'`, `'Molecules/Alert'`, `'Molecules/BaseModal'`, `'Molecules/CarOfferInputCard'`, `'Molecules/CompareTray'`, `'Molecules/ContentTile'`, `'Molecules/LocationTile'`, `'Molecules/LocationTileVdp'`, `'Molecules/CarouselDots'`, `'Molecules/FaqBlogTab'`, `'Molecules/ModalTabs'`, `'Molecules/SRPTile'`, `'Molecules/VdpGallery'`, `'Molecules/VdpSummary'`, plus **`'Molecules/SRP Filters/...'`** sub-folder: `FilterParent`, `FilterChild`, `FilterChildTextLink`, `SrpFilterPill`, `SrpFilterDistance`, `SrpLocationFlyIn`, `MakeModelTrimFilter`, `PricePaymentFilter`, `SrpFilterYear`, `SrpFilterMileage`, `SrpFilterFeatures`, `SrpFilterMpgEngine`, `SrpFilterDriveTrans`, `SrpFilterColor`, `SrpFilterCondition`, `SrpFilterVehicleStatus`
  - **Organisms** (flat): `'Organisms/GlobalHeader'`, `'Organisms/GlobalFooter'`, `'Organisms/SonicNavBar'`, `'Organisms/SRP Filters/FiltersPanel'`
  - **Pages** (`src/pages/`): `'Pages/SRP'`, `'Pages/VDP'` — full-page compositions showing components in context; each page story has per-brand variants (EchoPark + Sonic)
  - **Components**: reserved for future standalone app stories — none yet (keep `'Components'` in `preview.ts` `order` if you add some later)

## Figma MCP Workflow
1. **Select node in Figma** (Figma must be open and the desktop app focused)
2. **Generate component**: "generate a Vue component for this" →
   - Call `get_design_context` (clientFrameworks: "vue", clientLanguages: "typescript,css")
   - Call `get_screenshot` immediately after (required)
   - Convert React+Tailwind output → Vue SFC + CSS custom properties
   - Create `ComponentName.vue` + `ComponentName.stories.ts` + `index.ts`, then add the component to `src/index.ts`
3. **Extract tokens**: "extract tokens from this" →
   - Call `get_variable_defs` + `get_screenshot` simultaneously
   - If screenshot has values not in variable defs, call `get_design_context` for precise values
   - Update `tokens.css` and `tokens.ts`
4. **Single swatch**: Call `get_design_context` — exact hex is in `bg-[#xxxxxx]` Tailwind class
5. **Design system rules**: Call `create_design_system_rules` tool → update this rule file

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`BaseButton`, `FormInput`, `NavigationBar`)
- Props: camelCase; emits: camelCase (`"update:modelValue"`, `"click"`, `"dismiss"`)
- CSS custom properties: kebab-case matching Figma variable name pattern (see mapping above)
- Story titles: `'Atoms/…'`, `'Molecules/…'`, `'Organisms/…'`, `'Pages/…'`, `'Components/…'` — see Storybook Rules and `.storybook/preview.ts` sort order

## Icon & Logo System

### SVG loader setup
- **Plugin**: `vite-svg-loader` (`defaultImport: 'component'`) — used in `vite.config.ts` and `vite.lib.config.ts`
- **Aliases**: `@icons/` → `icon/`, `@logos/` → `Logos/`, `@illustrations/` → `Illustrations/`
- **Types**: `src/vite-env.d.ts` declares `*.svg?component` (Vue component), `*.svg?url` (string URL), and `*.svg?raw` (inline SVG string for `v-html` / icons inside styled wrappers)

### System icons (`icon/Style=*.svg`)
- 24×24, single-colour `fill="#242C33"`, always imported with `?component` query
- Filenames: `Style=<Category>, Detail=<Name>, Icon=<Variant>.svg` (original Figma export names, keep as-is)
- **In components that need colour inheritance**: use CSS `:deep()` combinator to override fill:
  ```css
  .my-wrapper :deep(path) { fill: currentColor; }
  ```
- **Gallery story**: `src/stories/Icons.stories.ts` (`Atoms/Icons`)

### Illustrative icons (`icon/Icon=Illustrative, Name=*.svg`)
- Multi-colour, used at larger display sizes — do NOT attempt to override colours

### Vehicle Descriptor icons (`icon/Icon Type=Vehicle Descriptors, *.svg`)
- Three size variants: Large (48px), Medium (32px), Small (16px)

### Logos (`Logos/`)
- Always import with `?url` to preserve multi-colour fills: `import epLogo from '@logos/Color=EP-FullColor.svg?url'`
- Use in `<img src="epLogo" alt="EchoPark" />` — NEVER as inline Vue component
- **EchoPark logos**: `Color=EP-FullColor.svg` (dark/standard), `Color=EP-GreenWhite.svg` (light-on-dark for transparent headers)
- **Sonic Automotive logos**: `Color=SA-FullColor.svg` (full-colour)
- **Gallery story**: `src/stories/Logos.stories.ts` (`Atoms/Logos`)
- Subdirectory `Logos/3rd Party/` contains partner/trust badge logos (same `?url` approach)

### Illustrations (`Illustrations/`)
- Multi-colour SVG illustrations for marketing content, empty states, and hero sections
- Naming: `Property 1=<Name>.svg` (1x) and `Property 1=<Name>@2x.svg` (retina)
- **SVG illustrations**: **Car**, **PersonDriving**, **HoldingACar**, **Variant4** — each in 1x and @2x
- **190-Point Inspection** (PNG): **Size=Badge**, **Size=Small**, **Size=Large** — raster badges at different display sizes
- **Finance** (PNG): **Financial institutions** — partner/lender imagery
- **GAP** (PNG): **GapCar** — split car image (half-grey insurance payout / half-green GAP coverage) used by `GapGraphic` component
- **Protection Plans** (PNG): **ProtectionPlansCar** — white sedan with transparent background, used by `ProtectionPlansGraphic` component
- Always import with `?url` to preserve fills: `import carIllustration from '@illustrations/Property 1=Car.svg?url'`
- Use in `<img>` — NEVER as inline Vue component (same pattern as logos)
- **Path alias**: `@illustrations/` → `Illustrations/`
- **Gallery story**: `src/stories/Illustrations.stories.ts` (`Atoms/Illustrations`) — "All Illustrations" (SVGs) and "Raster Images" (PNGs grouped by category)

### Photos (`Photos/`)
- Photography assets (PNG) organized by category subfolders
- **Categories**: `Car only/` (6), `EchoPark team/` (5), `Nascar promo/` (7), `People/` (14), `Service and protection/` (13), `VDP cars/` (4)
- Import with `?url` for use in `<img>` tags: `import hero from '/Photos/People/Hero image.png?url'`
- **Gallery story**: `src/stories/Photos.stories.ts` (`Atoms/Photos`) — one story per category + "All Photos" overview

## Accessibility
- Semantic HTML first; ARIA only when native semantics are insufficient
- All interactive components need correct roles/attributes
- Storybook a11y addon errors must be resolved before considering a component done
